{"id": 7528, "title": "Ticket #7528: startd doesn't advertise availability of avx512 instructions", "description": "<blockquote>\nNewer Intel cpus now support 512 bit vector instructions, the so-called avx512.  However, there are several subsets of these, and Linux doesn't advertise in the /proc/cpuinfo flags field just avx512, as HTCondor had assumed, rather it advertises the subsets, like avx512f.  Let's change HTCondor to correctly detect and advertise that a machine has avx512 instructions.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Oct-01 11:21</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/5abbebc9fe38a2b02e38399297cad6ab84252513\">[61386]</a></span>: Add avx512 slot ad flags to documentation <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7528\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7528'); return false;\" title=\"startd doesn't advertise availability of avx512 instructions\">#7528</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Feb-28 10:19</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/e8099e868995cff249f501008b1594bc21b38db1\">[59065]</a></span>: Document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7528\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7528'); return false;\" title=\"startd doesn't advertise availability of avx512 instructions\">#7528</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n